00:58:33,039 --> 00:58:33,839
Like you're not-

1304
00:58:34,879 --> 00:58:35,679
We're not here.

1305
00:58:35,679 --> 00:58:36,960
You're not being sneaky.

1306
00:58:36,960 --> 00:58:38,000
We're not here.

1307
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:39,199
You're talking right now.

1308
00:58:39,920 --> 00:58:40,420
Henry!

1309
00:58:44,239 --> 00:58:45,519
We're just working here.

1310
00:58:45,519 --> 00:58:46,319
We're not doing here.

1311
00:58:46,319 --> 00:58:47,279
What are you guys doing?

1312
00:58:47,279 --> 00:58:49,199
Not doing, not working.

1313
00:58:49,199 --> 00:58:49,920
Please leave us.

1314
00:58:50,319 --> 00:58:52,239
We don't mean you harm.

1315
00:58:52,239 --> 00:58:52,879
That's what they all say.

1316
00:58:52,879 --> 00:58:54,239
What are you guys doing in here?

1317
00:58:54,239 --> 00:58:55,440
Why aren't you attacking us?

1318
00:58:55,440 --> 00:58:59,519
Never have we met a group of kobolds that didn't want to just like get it on

1319
00:59:00,719 --> 00:59:03,039
in a fighting manner.

1320
00:59:03,039 --> 00:59:03,839
In like a-

1321
00:59:03,839 --> 00:59:05,679
In a non-sexual kind of way.

1322
00:59:05,679 --> 00:59:09,279
Yes, well, I mean, we're just workers.

1323
00:59:09,279 --> 00:59:18,000
We're just polishing and cleaning and making sure his giants are shiny and good.

1324
00:59:18,000 --> 00:59:19,359
You mean all these dead giants?

1325
00:59:19,360 --> 00:59:20,000
Yeah, yeah.

1326
00:59:20,000 --> 00:59:21,680
Well, you have to polish dead giants.

1327
00:59:25,440 --> 00:59:25,920
True that.

1328
00:59:25,920 --> 00:59:26,640
All right, yep.

1329
00:59:26,640 --> 00:59:27,599
Yeah, story checks out.

1330
00:59:27,599 --> 00:59:29,519
I read it in How to Keep a Good Lair.

1331
00:59:29,519 --> 00:59:30,800
That's what we convinced.

1332
00:59:30,800 --> 00:59:34,800
That's what we convinced him that we needs to do so he doesn't eat us.

1333
00:59:37,440 --> 00:59:39,039
Are you captives?

1334
00:59:40,400 --> 00:59:40,800
Maybe.

1335
00:59:40,800 --> 00:59:42,240
Or are you mercenaries?

1336
00:59:44,400 --> 00:59:45,360
We are workers.

1337
00:59:46,320 --> 00:59:47,680
How did you end up down here?

1338
00:59:47,680 --> 00:59:50,800
We were brought in by him.

1339
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:52,160
Could you be more specific?

1340
00:59:52,160 --> 00:59:53,280
By the dragon?

1341
00:59:53,280 --> 00:59:55,040
Yes, yes, by the dragon.

1342
00:59:56,320 --> 01:00:01,600
We were brought in by him and we look for guidance from him.

1343
01:00:01,600 --> 01:00:03,520
Have you seen the horned lady?

1344
01:00:05,600 --> 01:00:08,560
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

1345
01:00:09,840 --> 01:00:11,280
Can you guys show us where she is?

1346
01:00:11,280 --> 01:00:13,440
We'd like to talk with her.

1347
01:00:13,440 --> 01:00:14,880
We have work to do.

1348
01:00:15,519 --> 01:00:24,000
She, you leave and you go that way and they point right down the hall out the door.

1349
01:00:24,640 --> 01:00:25,760
I don't feel the need to murder.

1350
01:00:25,760 --> 01:00:26,960
Yeah, I'm good with it.

1351
01:00:26,960 --> 01:00:29,840
Me either, but let's just tie them up or something.

1352
01:00:30,480 --> 01:00:32,559
We can't just leave them wandering around, right?

1353
01:00:32,559 --> 01:00:33,280
Let's tie them up.

1354
01:00:33,280 --> 01:00:33,599
I don't know.

1355
01:00:33,599 --> 01:00:36,079
It seemed like they didn't really want anything to do with us.

1356
01:00:36,720 --> 01:00:44,160
Kobolds normally it's like a fight thing so if they're not wanting to fight or throw down.

1357
01:00:44,159 --> 01:00:45,359
I think we're good to just leave.

1358
01:00:45,359 --> 01:00:47,199
What if they will go warn the dragon?

1359
01:00:47,199 --> 01:00:48,000
You could leave us.

1360
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:49,279
We won't tell him.

1361
01:00:49,279 --> 01:00:51,920
I would think by now he probably knows we're already here.

1362
01:00:51,920 --> 01:00:53,039
Do you know if he knows we're here?

1363
01:00:53,679 --> 01:00:55,679
Knows who knows you're here?

1364
01:00:56,319 --> 01:00:57,920
Do you know if the dragon knows we're here?

1365
01:00:59,679 --> 01:01:01,199
Does the dragon know we're here?

1366
01:01:01,199 --> 01:01:04,960
Well, that was a very clear statement like as a question.

1367
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:09,199
In the grand scheme of things, who knows who's here?

1368
01:01:09,199 --> 01:01:10,719
Pretty philosophical.

1369
01:01:10,719 --> 01:01:11,679
He knows you're here.

1370
01:01:11,680 --> 01:01:12,640
Okay, thank you.

1371
01:01:12,640 --> 01:01:15,840
Yeah, just honesty is always the best.

1372
01:01:15,840 --> 01:01:17,040
He might know you're here.

1373
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:19,120
Are you Henry?

1374
01:01:19,120 --> 01:01:21,200
No, no, I'm Steve.

1375
01:01:21,200 --> 01:01:21,840
Okay, Steve.

1376
01:01:23,040 --> 01:01:24,160
Thanks for being honest, Steve.

1377
01:01:24,800 --> 01:01:25,440
You're welcome.

1378
01:01:25,440 --> 01:01:26,000
We won't murder you.

1379
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:29,360
Steve, you gonna get up in our business if we just leave you here not tied up?

1380
01:01:29,360 --> 01:01:32,000
Oh, we're just, yeah, don't tie.

1381
01:01:32,000 --> 01:01:33,040
We don't need to tie us.

1382
01:01:34,320 --> 01:01:35,920
You need rope for something else, right?

1383
01:01:36,720 --> 01:01:37,600
Probably.

1384
01:01:37,600 --> 01:01:40,000
Yeah, you seem like rope loving.

1385
01:01:40,719 --> 01:01:41,840
We do love rope.

1386
01:01:41,840 --> 01:01:43,360
Just hang on to your rope.

1387
01:01:44,480 --> 01:01:49,199
The major characteristic of our adventuring crew is the fact that we all love rope.

1388
01:01:49,199 --> 01:01:50,000
And fire.

1389
01:01:50,000 --> 01:01:52,559
Rope and fire make good combos, but not for cobbles.

1390
01:01:53,440 --> 01:01:54,559
I say we leave them.

1391
01:01:54,559 --> 01:01:55,119
All right.

1392
01:01:55,119 --> 01:01:55,760
Thank you.

1393
01:01:55,760 --> 01:01:56,719
Hey, no problem.

1394
01:01:56,719 --> 01:01:58,960
Remember this when we go to set everyone free down here.

1395
01:01:58,960 --> 01:02:00,559
You're set free?

1396
01:02:01,920 --> 01:02:02,880
Okay, bye.

1397
01:02:03,519 --> 01:02:08,960
Oh, but tell the dragon anything and I'll come back and let you all on fire.

1398
01:02:08,960 --> 01:02:10,480
Henry will tell nobody.

1399
01:02:10,480 --> 01:02:12,480
And what about Steve?

1400
01:02:12,480 --> 01:02:14,240
Steve tells everybody nothing.

1401
01:02:15,840 --> 01:02:17,039
Steve is the worst.

1402
01:02:18,480 --> 01:02:21,840
Okay, so just so you know, anyone tells the dragon anything,

1403
01:02:21,840 --> 01:02:24,480
I'm going to come back and light everyone on fire.

1404
01:02:24,480 --> 01:02:26,639
What if nobody tells the dragons nothing?

1405
01:02:27,360 --> 01:02:29,679
I just want to get away from all these total negatives.

1406
01:02:29,679 --> 01:02:32,639
How about I light one of you on fire just to make my point?

1407
01:02:32,639 --> 01:02:34,240
We tell nothing to dragons.

1408
01:02:34,240 --> 01:02:34,740
Perfect.

1409
01:02:35,280 --> 01:02:36,320
I'm not tired of this.

1410
01:02:36,320 --> 01:02:38,559
God, I just want to leave.

1411
01:02:39,920 --> 01:02:42,159
Okay, so you go right?

1412
01:02:42,159 --> 01:02:42,639
Yep.

1413
01:02:42,639 --> 01:02:43,199
We go right?

1414
01:02:43,199 --> 01:02:43,760
Yeah.

1415
01:02:43,760 --> 01:02:44,800
You enter.

1416
01:02:45,760 --> 01:02:49,440
You've got room two on your left, room 13 on your right.

1417
01:02:50,159 --> 01:02:54,159
Probably room 13 since her room is one of the ones along the back.

1418
01:02:54,159 --> 01:02:54,480
Yeah.

1419
01:02:54,480 --> 01:02:56,480
Let's go for room 13.

1420
01:02:56,480 --> 01:03:01,679
So a bizarre sight greets you in this rough walled chamber.

1421
01:03:01,679 --> 01:03:07,360
About a dozen giant toads with thick mottled white hides are at work here,

1422
01:03:08,320 --> 01:03:11,440
scribing strange writings into the ice of the walls

1423
01:03:12,720 --> 01:03:15,920
or onto weathered parchment and stone tablets.

1424
01:03:15,920 --> 01:03:22,320
A few toads transfer parchments and tablets into and out of floor to ceiling cubby holes

1425
01:03:22,320 --> 01:03:26,240
cut into the ice along the entire southern wall.

1426
01:03:26,880 --> 01:03:34,720
As you enter, a couple of them see you and call attention to all of the other ones

1427
01:03:34,720 --> 01:03:38,080
and they all start croaking very loudly at you.

1428
01:03:38,960 --> 01:03:40,000
I put my finger to my lips.

1429
01:03:43,680 --> 01:03:44,880
Did that do the job?

1430
01:03:44,880 --> 01:03:45,380
Anything?

1431
01:03:48,800 --> 01:03:56,160
A few of them flee into the back area, the room 14 for your map purposes,

1432
01:03:56,160 --> 01:03:59,280
and they start to quiet down a little bit.

1433
01:03:59,280 --> 01:04:00,000
Most of them.

1434
01:04:00,000 --> 01:04:04,560
Couple of them are still quite loud and kind of hopping around.

1435
01:04:05,120 --> 01:04:06,160
As toads do.

1436
01:04:08,160 --> 01:04:09,040
How big are they?

1437
01:04:09,040 --> 01:04:10,080
So they're hopping mad?

1438
01:04:11,520 --> 01:04:12,880
They are giant toads.

1439
01:04:12,880 --> 01:04:15,520
So they're a medium-sized creature.

1440
01:04:15,520 --> 01:04:20,160
So they're about, I would say about the size of a flint.

1441
01:04:20,160 --> 01:04:20,660
Hooray!

1442
01:04:22,160 --> 01:04:27,200
But actually just toads, not like bipedal creatures that look like toads.

1443
01:04:27,200 --> 01:04:28,080
That is correct.

1444
01:04:28,960 --> 01:04:32,320
And these are toads that are litter, like they're literate.

1445
01:04:33,280 --> 01:04:34,640
They're scribing something.

1446
01:04:36,640 --> 01:04:38,960
Can I try and animal handle them?

1447
01:04:38,960 --> 01:04:39,460
Sure.

1448
01:04:40,880 --> 01:04:42,880
But don't animal handle them, they don't like that.

1449
01:04:42,880 --> 01:04:44,080
Oh, rough call.

1450
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:46,080
19 plus 5, so 24.

1451
01:04:47,120 --> 01:04:51,280
So I like make soothing sounds like you would, you know,

1452
01:04:51,280 --> 01:04:54,880
like to a horse or a dog that you don't know, like shh shh shh.

1453
01:04:54,880 --> 01:04:58,240
We're not here to hurt you, just want to know what's going on.

1454
01:04:58,240 --> 01:05:03,520
We're looking for our friend, the horned lady?

1455
01:05:03,520 --> 01:05:05,680
They begin croaking again.

1456
01:05:06,720 --> 01:05:08,080
Make an intelligence check.

1457
01:05:09,040 --> 01:05:10,080
Anybody can.

1458
01:05:10,080 --> 01:05:12,320
Well I only got a 10, so I hope somebody does better.

1459
01:05:12,320 --> 01:05:13,120
I got a 7.

1460
01:05:13,120 --> 01:05:13,620
12?

1461
01:05:14,640 --> 01:05:15,840
Wait it got flint!

1462
01:05:15,840 --> 01:05:16,800
All right.

1463
01:05:16,800 --> 01:05:22,400
It appears that they are trying to communicate with you.

1464
01:05:24,240 --> 01:05:26,640
You can't quite make out what they're trying to say.

1465
01:05:26,639 --> 01:05:30,239
You don't recognize what they're saying as a language.

1466
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:34,319
Can I make a perception check and see if I can recognize

1467
01:05:34,319 --> 01:05:37,279
a language in which they were transcribing things onto the wall?

1468
01:05:37,279 --> 01:05:38,079
Yep.

1469
01:05:38,079 --> 01:05:39,199
Oh, fuck.

1470
01:05:40,480 --> 01:05:41,279
Four.

1471
01:05:41,279 --> 01:05:42,319
I did that as well.

1472
01:05:43,839 --> 01:05:44,879
Did you say four?

1473
01:05:44,879 --> 01:05:45,199
Yeah.

1474
01:05:45,199 --> 01:05:46,079
Yeah, I rolled a four.

1475
01:05:47,199 --> 01:05:48,239
What's the thing?

1476
01:05:48,239 --> 01:05:49,519
An intelligence, do you think?

1477
01:05:50,239 --> 01:05:52,960
No, just perception.

1478
01:05:53,599 --> 01:05:54,639
Wisdom perception, yeah.

1479
01:05:54,879 --> 01:05:57,119
Okay, well then my four turns into an 11.

1480
01:05:59,199 --> 01:06:00,799
I have a 16 then.

1481
01:06:00,799 --> 01:06:01,599
Nicely done.

1482
01:06:01,599 --> 01:06:05,599
You don't recognize the language that it's being written in.

1483
01:06:06,239 --> 01:06:07,599
Like is that even draconic?

1484
01:06:08,239 --> 01:06:10,000
It's not draconic that they're writing in.

1485
01:06:10,000 --> 01:06:12,000
Or giant or orcish or goblin?

1486
01:06:12,000 --> 01:06:14,960
Or giant or orcish or goblin.

1487
01:06:14,960 --> 01:06:15,279
Okay.

1488
01:06:15,279 --> 01:06:16,639
What about dwarven?

1489
01:06:16,639 --> 01:06:17,759
Is it celestial?

1490
01:06:18,719 --> 01:06:20,079
It's not celestial.

1491
01:06:21,279 --> 01:06:24,079
I'm pretty sure none of you have it, but let me just double check.

1492
01:06:24,079 --> 01:06:24,960
Is it druidic?

1493
01:06:25,920 --> 01:06:26,239
No.

1494
01:06:26,239 --> 01:06:27,679
I just said all mine.

1495
01:06:27,679 --> 01:06:30,159
So if it's not those, I don't have it.

1496
01:06:30,159 --> 01:06:30,880
Same, Zeus.

1497
01:06:30,880 --> 01:06:33,119
Guys, turns out they were writing in common the whole time.

1498
01:06:33,759 --> 01:06:35,199
Again, I didn't ask about that.

1499
01:06:35,199 --> 01:06:36,639
Well, what about Donnie though?

1500
01:06:36,639 --> 01:06:43,279
Because he can speak telepathically, so can he try to send them like...

1501
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:47,119
Like a smiley face and a peace sign and a dove?

1502
01:06:47,119 --> 01:06:47,279
Yeah, exactly.

1503
01:06:47,279 --> 01:06:50,079
Like pictures or something.

1504
01:06:50,079 --> 01:06:52,319
The universal sign for you want to get high.

1505
01:06:52,319 --> 01:06:53,440
Something pictogrammy.

1506
01:06:53,440 --> 01:06:54,639
And a thumbs up.

1507
01:06:54,639 --> 01:06:55,360
Yes.

1508
01:06:55,360 --> 01:06:58,240
And like a finger to your lips like shh.

1509
01:06:58,240 --> 01:06:58,960
Yes.

1510
01:06:58,960 --> 01:06:59,679
All of that.

1511
01:06:59,679 --> 01:07:00,639
I love all of that.

1512
01:07:01,840 --> 01:07:07,440
He does something along those lines, but he tells you...

1513
01:07:08,480 --> 01:07:11,599
Guys, I think they do speak draconic.

1514
01:07:12,720 --> 01:07:14,720
They're very slow when they speak.

1515
01:07:14,720 --> 01:07:15,200
It takes...

1516
01:07:16,480 --> 01:07:17,840
It's painful to listen to.

1517
01:07:19,039 --> 01:07:20,800
I mean, they're toads, so...

1518
01:07:21,680 --> 01:07:22,180
Yeah.

1519
01:07:23,360 --> 01:07:29,760
He says that they do have a leader who sometimes speaks more better, as they put it.

1520
01:07:30,640 --> 01:07:31,920
Maybe we can try and talk to him?

1521
01:07:32,640 --> 01:07:33,120
Sure.

1522
01:07:33,120 --> 01:07:38,160
In draconic, really slowly, I say, take me to your leader.

1523
01:07:50,800 --> 01:08:01,519
Music in today's episode was by Kavin McLeod of incompetech.filmmusic.io.

1524
01:08:01,519 --> 01:08:06,160
Dumbgeons and Dragons is a Dumb Dragons production.
